6.1 base

# Create data
set.seed(1234)
data <- data.frame(x1=sample(seq(1,15),10), x2=sample(seq(1,15),10), x3=sample(seq(1,15),10))
# Add line on top
plot(data$x1, col="darkblue", type="l", lwd=3, xlab="", ylab="",ylim=c(0,15), pch=20)

# Çizgi grafik
plot(data$x1, col="darkblue", type="l", lwd=3, xlab="", ylab="",ylim=c(0,15), pch=20)
# Alanı renklendirme
polygon( 
  c(1, 1:10 ,10), 
  c(0, data$x1, 0), 
  col="lightblue", border=F)

Birden fazla değişkenin alan grafiğiyle gösterimi

# 1. çizgi grafik
plot(data$x1, col=rgb(60,164,131, maxColorValue = 255), type="l", lwd=3, xlab="", ylab="",ylim=c(0,15), pch=20)

# üstüste çizmek için
par(new=TRUE) 
# 2. çizgi grafik
plot(data$x2, col=rgb(248,56,25, maxColorValue = 255), type="l", lwd=3, xlab="", ylab="",ylim=c(0,15), pch=20)
par(new=TRUE) 
# 3. çizgi grafik
plot(data$x3, col=rgb(24,105,109, maxColorValue = 255), type="l", lwd=3, xlab="", ylab="",ylim=c(0,15), pch=20)
# 1. çizgi için
polygon(c(1,1:10,10),y=c(0,data$x1,0),
  col=rgb(60,164,131, maxColorValue = 255, alpha = 60), border=F)
# 2. çizgi için 
polygon(c(1,1:10,10),y=c(0,data$x2,0),
  col=rgb(248,56,25, maxColorValue = 255, alpha = 60), border=F)
# 3. çizgi için 
polygon(c(1,1:10,10),y=c(0,data$x3,0),
  col=rgb(24,105,109, maxColorValue = 255, alpha = 60), border=F)

areaplot(formula, data, subset, na.action = NULL, ...)

6.4 ggplot2

library(ggplot2)

# create data
xValue <- 1:50
yValue <- cumsum(rnorm(50))
data <- data.frame(xValue,yValue)

# Plot
ggplot(data, aes(x=xValue, y=yValue)) +
  geom_area()

library(ggplot2)
library(hrbrthemes)
## NOTE: Either Arial Narrow or Roboto Condensed fonts are required to use these themes.
##       Please use hrbrthemes::import_roboto_condensed() to install Roboto Condensed and
##       if Arial Narrow is not on your system, please see https://bit.ly/arialnarrow
# create data
xValue <- 1:10
yValue <- abs(cumsum(rnorm(10)))
data <- data.frame(xValue,yValue)

# Plot
ggplot(data, aes(x=xValue, y=yValue)) +
  geom_area( fill="#69b3a2", alpha=0.4) +
  geom_line(color="#69b3a2", size=2) +
  geom_point(size=3, color="#69b3a2") +
  theme_ipsum() +
  ggtitle("Evolution of something")

d1=data.frame(year, name, value)
library(dplyr)
